claim: Recombinant HA antigens produced using BEVS have been shown to induce significantly higher levels of broadly cross-reactive antibodies against highly conserved regions of HA compared with egg-derived vaccines.
explanation: A table listing influenza vaccine virus strains (by strain name and lineage), production method (cell-derived vs egg-derived candidate vaccine viruses), and the specific hemagglutinin (HA) amino acid substitutions observed at various HA residue positions for each strain. does not support the claim — the table only documents egg-adapted amino acid substitutions in HA for different cell- and egg-derived vaccine viruses and contains no data on recombinant HA produced in BEVS or any antibody response measurements. Note: The table is legible, but it provides sequence information only, with no immunogenicity or BEVS data to assess cross-reactive antibody levels.
